Package loopingandcollections

Class Dog

  • java.lang.Object
    • loopingandcollections.Dog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Dog>
    public class Dog
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Dog>
    A class that contains some characteristics of Dogs. Used to demonstrate how collections handle objects. interface Comparable is implemented so an Array of Dog can be sorted. Otherwise Comparable interface and the compareTo method are not needed!

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo​(Dog o)
        Add this override when implementing comparable
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Dog>
        Parameters:
        o - the object to compare to this object
        Returns:
        0, 1, -1 depending on comparing of object
        comparable actually works this way
        returns 0 if the primitive types compared are the same
        No change in order
        returns 1 if the current field is greater than the one being compared,
        so move the current object after the one being compared
        else returns -1 we know the current field is less than the one being compared,
        so move the object ahead of the object being compared
        logic to implement this is built into the Array.sort method
